{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the large envelope protein S from hepatitis B virus. The large envelope protein exists in two topological conformations, one which is termed 'external' or Le-HBsAg and the other 'internal' or Li-HBsAg. In its external conformation the protein attaches the virus to cell receptors and thereby initiating infection. This interaction determines the species specificity and liver tropism. In its internal conformation the protein plays a role in virion morphogenesis and mediates the contact with the nucleocapsid like a matrix protein [[cite:PUB00087120], [cite:PUB00087119], [cite:PUB00087121]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"hamap" {"MF_04075" "Large envelope protein [S]"}, "pfam" {"PF00695" "Major surface antigen from hepadnavirus"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Large envelope protein S", "short" "HBV_HBSAG"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 13, "proteomes" 19, "taxa" 198, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 63008, "sets" 0, "proteins" 62508, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR000349", :literature {"PUB00087120" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Block TM" "Lu X" "Mehta A" "Park J" "Blumberg BS" "Dwek R."], "ISO_journal" "Adv. Exp. Med. Biol.", "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "Adv Exp Med Biol", "title" "Role of glycan processing in hepatitis B virus envelope protein trafficking.", "year" 1998, "raw_pages" "207-16", "volume" "435", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 9498079}, "PUB00087119" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Bruss V."], "ISO_journal" "Virus Res.", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.virusres.2004.08.016", "medline_journal" "Virus Res", "title" "Envelopment of the hepatitis B virus nucleocapsid.", "year" 2004, "